Description: Sherd of disc foot of Attic black-glazed pottery kylix; heavy build with convex edge; glazed black on exterior and underside; reserved outer face of foot and resting surface; traces of band in added red (faded) around perimeter on top surface; inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1495)
